<statement>
<p>
A population of bacteria is growing according to the equation <m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1600}{e}^{{{0.16}{t}}}</m>.  Estimate when the population will exceed 2545.</p>
<p>
<em>t</em>= <fillin characters="20" /> Â  </p>
<p>
Give your answer accurate to one decimal place.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>2.9007938797297</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1600}{e}^{{{0.16}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{2545}={1600}{e}^{{{0.16}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{2545}}{{1600}}={e}^{{{0.16}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{\ln{{\left(\frac{{2545}}{{1600}}\right)}}}={0.16}{t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{\ln{{\left(\frac{{2545}}{{1600}}\right)}}}}{{0.16}}={t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{t}={2.9007938797297}</m></p>
</solution>
